-- Copper in New York Drops to One-Month Low After Greece Credit Rating Cut
-- Wendy Pugh
-- 2010-04-27T23:50:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/copper-in-new-york-drops-to-one-month-low-after-greece-credit-rating-cut.html

          
          
                  April 28 (Bloomberg) - Copper futures in New York dropped
as much as 0.7 percent to the lowest since March 26. The
contract reached $3.3585 a pound before trading at $3.3770 at
9:46 a.m. Melbourne time.  
